<subSubSection id="9C8FAF351CEBB6C68EB3C801FF199F85" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="50649A2B6F61BFE9DEFF6F9893924EB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E2A73681BC2387B9BD8B11E6EB6DF5B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A very rare species endemic to northern Andean Peru only known from the type collection.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="849398EEB1DF7CF8FC430A737F912FA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="5D5FB48A09BA2374759AAACF49BBA40E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">PERU. Amazonas</emphasis>
: The type collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="16ECC9C10C3A00B5359627CF8ADF5BE6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="2AC9CE1C9B96D3BF4F06159C96010365" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA5FBEBB11C50A8B5AF58113C458EF8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Appears to be rather similar vegetatively to 
<taxonomicName id="53C36BFB7742D8EB8C452493C3C11934" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="praecana">
<emphasis id="B635E04F9868F6D5FF466946BCD0179E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea praecana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially in the leaf shape, indumentum and short peduncles, but differs in the longer, clearly funnel-shaped, pink corolla.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
